<br>
There's one obvious way to get rid of Team Manaburn farming Kunark dragons for phat lewtz, without horribly crippling Manaburn's power.<br>
<br>
Let manaburn hit anything, but if manaburn alone(and this counts all manaburns) does more than 50%(or some other appropriate percentage), then the mob leaves no loot and gives no exp.  Similiar to how merchants work.<br>
<br>
Small guilds with only one or two manaburn capable wizards would still benefit from the skill.<br>
<br>
Manaburn would still be useful to take down that normal mob(like the CHing cleric) immediately.<br>
<br>
The only thing that would change is there would be no more groups of wizards porting into the Dreadlands five minutes after Gore pops.<br>
<br>
