<br>
a) players boasting their kills on sont &amp; co is certainly a very bad idea.<br>
b) players farming kunark dragons might draw unwanted attention<br>
c) as AE groups didn't attract too much attention until it could  influence negatively other players (AEs in seb, sont farming) I have the distinct impression that nerfs don't happen until someone or multiple players bring up specifically situations where new abilities like MB in this case might ruin the game for others.<br>
Someone might argue that it doesn't. Some might argue that the power and  adrenaline rush is deserved for those 17 aa points or for the fact that it majorly sucked to be a wiz for a long time?<br>
Some will point out that all the other classes can have 100+ aa points and never have anything coming remotely close to what MB can do. <br>
<br>
If this goes live, to me it will be for these reasons.<br>
The ability of the sorcerers to bring up an alternate option other than 'fuck you verant' or 'nerf CH u beeeetch' might go a long way in the right ago, let alone getting other classes support.<br>
